Customer_Service: I haven't actually spoken with anyone from a car rental organization for quite a while.  When I did (probably about three years ago), I believe they were polite enough. However, I always hate to wait in lines when we have a lot of luggage.
Customer_Service_CN: 实际上，我已经有一段时间没有与汽车租赁组织的任何人交谈了。当我这样做时（大约三年前），我相信他们足够有礼貌。然而，当我们有很多行李时，我总是讨厌排队等候。

Customer_Service: They were too pushy in trying to sell insurance.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们在推销保险方面过于咄咄逼人。

Customer_Service: speed up the rental process!

Customer_Service: The counter girl seemed confused and she had lost our reservations. They directed us to one car and then came running out to tell us that was the wrong car and to come back to the counter. Getting directions took forever and they weren't accurate.
Customer_Service_CN: 柜台小姐似乎很困惑，她失去了我们的预订。他们引导我们到一辆车，然后跑出来告诉我们那辆车是错误的，并让我们回到柜台。获取路线花了很长时间而且不准确。

Customer_Service: For the most part, they it's been really good service.  I usually rent from the airports because it's much cheaper.  Once they charged me over and I had to hunt down the accounting department to get my money back.  it was a pain.
Customer_Service_CN: 在大多数情况下，他们的服务非常好。我通常从机场租房，因为便宜得多。有一次他们向我收费，我不得不去找会计部门要回我的钱。这是一种痛苦。

Customer_Service: I HATE how they pressure you to buy add-on service.
Customer_Service_CN: 我讨厌他们如何迫使你购买附加服务。

Customer_Service: took a long time to check in, and it would have been nice if someone explained how to get the convertible top down.
Customer_Service_CN: 花了很长时间才办理入住，如果有人解释一下如何打开敞篷车顶就好了。

Customer_Service: The agents were not friendly when I checked in initially, that was annoying because I had just spent 3 hours on a plane and wanted to be greeted with a better attitude.
Customer_Service_CN: 当我最初办理登机手续时，工作人员并不友好，这很烦人，因为我刚刚在飞机上呆了 3 个小时，希望得到更好的态度。

Customer_Service: they were a little slow

Customer_Service_CN: 我不得不排队等待很长时间才能取车和还车。另外，车子也不干净。

Customer_Service_CN: 人们普遍都很好，但工作过度。打印机坏了。那位可怜的收银员正要拔掉自己的头发。顾客对她大喊大叫，而不是我，但她不负责这些问题。

Customer_Service: The car I reserved was not ready.
Customer_Service_CN: 我预订的车还没有准备好。

Customer_Service: Had problems with windshield wipers that affected usability.  Problem was not solved.  Customer service was NOT helpful. Because of franchising, I was not able to get help from an office other than the one I rented from.  I had driven 60 miles from that location and there was another location 2 miles from where I was staying.
Customer_Service_CN: 挡风玻璃刮水器存在问题，影响了可用性。问题没有解决。客户服务没有帮助。由于特许经营，我无法从我租用的办公室以外的办公室获得帮助。我从那个地点开车 60 英里，距离我住的地方 2 英里还有另一个地点。

Customer_Service: I thought that they were very short and not very friendly. I felt like they hated their job and could care less about the customer.
Customer_Service_CN: 我觉得他们很矮而且不太友好。我觉得他们讨厌自己的工作并且不太关心客户。

Customer_Service: You need more staff to accommodate travelers who are in a hurry. Specifically, cut down the wait time to either retrieve or turn in a rental car.
Customer_Service_CN: 您需要更多的工作人员来接待匆忙的旅客。具体来说，减少取回或归还租赁汽车的等待时间。

Customer_Service: More agents during peak hours
Customer_Service_CN: 高峰时段代理较多

Customer_Service: Most windows were closed.
Customer_Service_CN: 大多数窗户都关着。

Customer_Service: the agent obviously hates their job more than I hate mine and that surprises me

Customer_Service: long lines waiting for the rental pick.

Customer_Service: it seems that they never have the class of car that I ordered.  also, the last time I got there earlier than I thought and they wouldn't let me have the car until the time that I had requested it because their computer wouldn't allow it.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们似乎从来没有我订购的汽车级别。另外，上次我到达那里的时间比我想象的要早，他们直到我提出请求时才让我拥有这辆车，因为他们的计算机不允许。

Customer_Service: The better the Customer service, the more likely it will be for me to rent from that company again  they should learn from this
Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务越好，我再次从该公司租赁的可能性就越大，他们应该从中吸取教训

Customer_Service: It was not as bad as it usually is.
Customer_Service_CN: 情况并不像平常那么糟糕。

Customer_Service: slow and stupid
Customer_Service_CN: 又慢又蠢

Customer_Service: Customer Service at Alamo was RUDE. We waited in line for over an hour to get our car. Car was bad. Had to change it few days later. Another family traveling with us was upgraded to a larger car as they were out of the type of car booked.

Customer_Service: Customer is important for the enjoyment of the car.  If it's a bad experience we won't return to that company if we can avoid it - they should remember abotut this
Customer_Service_CN: 客户对于汽车的享受非常重要。如果这是一次糟糕的经历，如果我们可以避免的话，我们就不会回到那家公司 - 他们应该记住这一点

Customer_Service_CN: 我上次租车是在新罕布什尔州曼彻斯特机场，他们在那里不再有办事处了

Customer_Service: Waiting line is too long.  They need to speed up the process.
Customer_Service_CN: 等候队伍太长。他们需要加快这一进程。

Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务代表说她没有可用的预留型号，我必须付费升级到其他型号。我拒绝了，然后免费获得了升级型号。

Customer_Service: Penalties for smoking in non-smoking cars should be more severe, and include decapitation.  Customer service was not receptive.
Customer_Service_CN: 在无烟车内吸烟的处罚应该更严厉，包括斩首。客户服务不热情。

Customer_Service: My main concern was that the price quoted on the internet was not the price that I was invoiced.   I had to call the provider and straighten it out but it took time and was a hassle.

Customer_Service: the better the customer service, the sooner the vacation starts
Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务越好，假期开始越早

Customer_Service: Customer service is horrible. I reserved through on-line which did not indicate/state I had to provide proof of insurance during pickup. The manager denied the reservation and after long and rude argument he finally gave in.
Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务很糟糕。我通过在线预订，但没有表明/声明我必须在取货时提供保险证明。经理拒绝了预订，经过长时间粗鲁的争论后，他终于屈服了。

Customer_Service: Slow, long lineup
Customer_Service_CN: 缓慢而漫长的队伍

Customer_Service: My last car rental was in Costa Rica.  There was lots of red tape associated with renting the car, it took almost an hour.  I don't usually experience that type of problem in the US.
Customer_Service_CN: 我最后一次租车是在哥斯达黎加。租车有很多繁文缛节，花了将近一个小时。我在美国通常不会遇到此类问题。

Customer_Service: Everyone was very helpful.  The car was ready for me on time and I didn't have to wait a long time at the counter.
Customer_Service_CN: 每个人都非常有帮助。车准时为我准备好了，我不用在柜台等太久。

Customer_Service: They moved me in and out quickly. The shuttle driver drove like a maniac.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们很快就把我搬进搬出。班车司机像个疯子一样开着车。

Customer_Service: We needed a minivan on very short notice to drive out of town to a funeral.  Enterprise staff worked hard to find us one, and they did. We smashed the car into a parking garage pole.  Since we had purchased the comprehensive insurance we didn't have to go through all of the B.S.
Customer_Service_CN: 我们需要一辆小型货车在很短的时间内开车出城参加葬礼。企业工作人员努力为我们找到了一个，他们做到了。我们把车撞到了停车场的杆子上。由于我们购买了综合保险，所以我们不必经历所有的BS

Customer_Service: The representatives were helpful and considerate
Customer_Service_CN: 代表们乐于助人且体贴

Customer_Service: Customer service was average.  They did not go above and beyond.  They did, however, do more than the minimum.
Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务很一般。他们并没有超越。然而，他们所做的超出了最低限度。

Customer_Service: Everything was great.  The line was a little long to get the car but it was a good experience.
Customer_Service_CN: 一切都很棒。取车的队伍有点长，但这是一次很好的体验。

Customer_Service: not applicable
Customer_Service_CN: 不适用

Customer_Service: they were trying to satisfy me even though my wife tells me I was being rude
Customer_Service_CN: 尽管我的妻子告诉我我很粗鲁，但他们还是试图让我满意

Customer_Service: friendly people
Customer_Service_CN: 友好的人

Customer_Service: They provided the best service thus far. They are very friendly and helpful. I have rented from other companies before both cheaper and more expensive.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们提供了迄今为止最好的服务。他们非常友好和乐于助人。我以前租过其他公司的，有便宜的，也有贵的。

Customer_Service: We had a small problem with the size of car we reserved being available. The company was able to send another car over from a different location. We were delayed in getting on the road, but were satisfied with the car.
Customer_Service_CN: 我们遇到了一个小问题，就是我们预订的汽车的大小可用。该公司能够从不同的地点派出另一辆车。我们上路耽误了，但对车很满意。

Customer_Service: None I  rarely rent cars
Customer_Service_CN: 没有 我很少租车

Customer_Service: they were extremely helpful and did whatever they could to help us.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们非常乐于助人，并竭尽全力帮助我们。

Customer_Service: the service at the airport was very convenient.  no lines at the service desk.
Customer_Service_CN: 机场的服务很方便。服务台无需排队。

Customer_Service: long lines moved quickly
Customer_Service_CN: 长队快速移动

Customer_Service: They had the class of car that I ordered.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们有我订购的汽车级别。

Customer_Service: No complaints.
Customer_Service_CN: 没什么好抱怨的。

Customer_Service: very limited (which is good).  quickly received car.
Customer_Service_CN: 非常有限（这很好）。很快就收到车了。

Customer_Service: they were fast and friendly.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们快速而友好。

Customer_Service: I never had to deal with customer service. The bus dropped me off at my car, when I returned the car, I had my receipt at that moment. I then got on the bus and left. Never having to wait in a line for customer service.
Customer_Service_CN: 我从来不需要处理客户服务。巴士把我送到了我的车旁，当我还车时，我当时就拿到了收据。然后我就上了公共汽车离开了。无需排队等待客户服务。

Customer_Service: Very nice, free upgrade
Customer_Service_CN: 非常好，免费升级

Customer_Service: Customer service was extremely helpful.  They knew I was visiting my 91 year old mother and upgraded at no cost to a car that would be more comfortable for her.
Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务非常有帮助。他们知道我正在探望我 91 岁的母亲，并免费升级了一辆对她来说更舒适的汽车。

Customer_Service: Well since I used to work for a car rental company and at the time I rented I was still working with the company, I was treated with nothing but respect and received a free upgrade as well.

Customer_Service: Last time I rented a car was when I went skiing with my whole family.  We got a Chevy Blazer.  We didn't think it was as large as a Ford Explorer, so we asked to switch.  The agent was very nice and gave us the Ford Explorer.
Customer_Service_CN: 上次租车是和全家人去滑雪的时候。我们有一辆雪佛兰开拓者。我们认为它没有福特探险者那么大，所以我们要求换。代理人很好，给了我们福特探险者。

Customer_Service: I did everything on-line - never talked to an agent during booking.  There were no problems, even though I had to switch car sizes after initial reservation. Agent on duty for pick-up was courteous.
Customer_Service_CN: 我在网上完成了所有事情 - 在预订期间从未与代理商交谈过。没有任何问题，尽管我在最初预订后不得不更换汽车尺寸。值班接机人员很有礼貌。

Customer_Service: I recently rented a car and they were outstanding.  The customer service rep was very helpful and courteous.  They even let me extend my rental by a couple of hours for no charge at all. I was very pleased with my experience and I would go back.
Customer_Service_CN: 我最近租了一辆车，它们非常出色。客户服务代表非常乐于助人而且很有礼貌。他们甚至让我免费延长租期几个小时。我对我的经历非常满意，我会回去。

Customer_Service: Wonderful experience - the rental and whole process was seamless

Customer_Service: I haven't actually spoken with anyone from a car rental organization for quite a while.  When I did (probably about three years ago), I believe they were polite enough. However, I always hate to wait in lines when we have a lot of luggage.
Customer_Service_CN: 实际上，我已经有一段时间没有与汽车租赁组织的任何人交谈了。当我这样做时（大约三年前），我相信他们足够有礼貌。然而，当我们有很多行李时，我总是讨厌排队等候。

Customer_Service: They were too pushy in trying to sell insurance.

Customer_Service_CN: 柜台小姐似乎很困惑，她失去了我们的预订。他们引导我们到一辆车，然后跑出来告诉我们那辆车是错误的，并让我们回到柜台。获取路线花了很长时间而且不准确。

Customer_Service: For the most part, they it's been really good service.  I usually rent from the airports because it's much cheaper.  Once they charged me over and I had to hunt down the accounting department to get my money back.  it was a pain.
Customer_Service_CN: 在大多数情况下，他们的服务非常好。我通常从机场租房，因为便宜得多。有一次他们向我收费，我不得不去找会计部门要回我的钱。这是一种痛苦。

Customer_Service: I HATE how they pressure you to buy add-on service.
Customer_Service_CN: 我讨厌他们如何迫使你购买附加服务。

Customer_Service: took a long time to check in, and it would have been nice if someone explained how to get the convertible top down.
Customer_Service_CN: 花了很长时间才办理入住，如果有人解释一下如何打开敞篷车顶就好了。

Customer_Service_CN: 当我最初办理登机手续时，工作人员并不友好，这很烦人，因为我刚刚在飞机上呆了 3 个小时，希望得到更好的态度。

Customer_Service: they were a little slow

Customer_Service_CN: 我不得不排队等待很长时间才能取车和还车。另外，车子也不干净。

Customer_Service_CN: 人们普遍都很好，但工作过度。打印机坏了。那位可怜的收银员正要拔掉自己的头发。顾客对她大喊大叫，而不是我，但她不负责这些问题。

Customer_Service: The car I reserved was not ready.
Customer_Service_CN: 我预订的车还没有准备好。

Customer_Service: Had problems with windshield wipers that affected usability.  Problem was not solved.  Customer service was NOT helpful. Because of franchising, I was not able to get help from an office other than the one I rented from.  I had driven 60 miles from that location and there was another location 2 miles from where I was staying.

Customer_Service: I thought that they were very short and not very friendly. I felt like they hated their job and could care less about the customer.

Customer_Service: You need more staff to accommodate travelers who are in a hurry. Specifically, cut down the wait time to either retrieve or turn in a rental car.

Customer_Service_CN: 高峰时段代理较多

Customer_Service: Most windows were closed.
Customer_Service_CN: 大多数窗户都关着。

Customer_Service: the agent obviously hates their job more than I hate mine and that surprises me

Customer_Service: it seems that they never have the class of car that I ordered.  also, the last time I got there earlier than I thought and they wouldn't let me have the car until the time that I had requested it because their computer wouldn't allow it.
Customer_Service_CN: 他们似乎从来没有我订购的汽车级别。另外，上次我到达那里的时间比我想象的要早，他们直到我提出请求时才让我拥有这辆车，因为他们的计算机不允许。

Customer_Service: The better the Customer service, the more likely it will be for me to rent from that company again  they should learn from this
Customer_Service_CN: 客户服务越好，我再次从该公司租赁的可能性就越大，他们应该从中吸取教训

Customer_Service: It was not as bad as it usually is.
Customer_Service_CN: 情况并不像平常那么糟糕。

Customer_Service: slow and stupid

Customer_Service: Customer is important for the enjoyment of the car.  If it's a bad experience we won't return to that company if we can avoid it - they should remember abotut this
Customer_Service_CN: 客户对于汽车的享受非常重要。如果这是一次糟糕的经历，如果我们可以避免的话，我们就不会回到那家公司 - 他们应该记住这一点

Customer_Service: Waiting line is too long.  They need to speed up the process.
Customer_Service_CN: 等候队伍太长。他们需要加快这一进程。

Customer_Service: Penalties for smoking in non-smoking cars should be more severe, and include decapitation.  Customer service was not receptive.

Customer_Service: the better the customer service, the sooner the vacation starts
